title: Mantoloking closer to dune project as state eyes holdouts
text: MANTOLOKING, N.J. (AP) - The Jersey shore town hardest hit by Superstorm Sandy is closer to getting protective sand dunes that many of its oceanfront homeowners didn't want. Of those 128 oceanfront homes, Mantoloking has completed property assessments for the last 10 holdouts who won't sign easements for the work ... ...
